{"title":"Shimano unveils ultra-limited centennial product","link":"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/shimano-unveils-ultra-limited-centennial-product/","date":1616372520000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>For months, a clock has been ticking down on a <a href=\"https://www.shimano.com/en/100th/\">Shimano Centennial website</a>, leading to <a href=\"https://www.cyclingnews.com/features/new-shimano-dura-ace-what-do-we-know-so-far/\">intense speculation</a> as to how the company would mark the milestone of its 100th year.&nbsp;After all, this is a titan of the cycling industry –&nbsp;godfathers of the acronym, inventors of <a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2020/07/an-ode-to-the-shimano-pd-m520-the-worlds-most-reliable-pedal/\">SPD</a>, Di2, STI.</p><p>Yesterday, the special Shimano Countdown Clock struck zero, and the answer was finally revealed.&nbsp;</p><p>It is stealthy. It is stylish. It is limited to 2,000 units.&nbsp;</p><p>It is … <a href=\"https://www.shimano.com/en/100th/100works/\">a coffee-table book</a>.&nbsp;</p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"697\" src=\"data:image/image/jpeg;base64,\" data-src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-2.52.56-pm-1340x697.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-srcset=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-2.52.56-pm-1340x697.jpg 1340w, https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-2.52.56-pm-650x338.jpg 650w, https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-2.52.56-pm-190x99.jpg 190w, https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-2.52.56-pm-1080x562.jpg 1080w, https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-2.52.56-pm-16x8.jpg 16w, https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Screen-Shot-2021-03-22-at-2.52.56-pm.jpg 1857w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\"><figcaption>Image: Shimano.</figcaption></figure><p>More specifically, it is the chance to enter a lottery to secure the right to buy a copy of the book, titled ‘Shimano 100 Works’. Successful applicants will find out in early June if they have earned the right to spend 10,000 Yen (AU$119 / US$92, inclusive of international shipping) on the 264-page volume, which Shimano estimates will begin shipping in September.&nbsp;</p><p>Admittedly, extreme close-up photos of shiny vintage fishing reels and bike parts may not be the centennial product you were dreaming of –&nbsp;even if it is perfect-bound, on semi-gloss stock –&nbsp;but it’s what Shimano has decided you deserve* (<em>*the right to enter a lottery to maybe buy</em>,<em> if you’re very lucky and have “reached the age of adulthood in the country / region of the sales destination</em>.”)</p><p>Looking on the bright side, it’s certainly cheaper than a trickle-down Di2 groupset, and more limited than the new 12-speed Dura Ace will be (whenever it actually comes out).</p><div data-block-name=\"highlight-box\" id=\"\"><p><em>To secure a headscratching piece of history, sign up for the lottery at <a href=\"https://www.shimano.com/en/100th/100works/\">Shimano.com</a>. May the odds be ever in your favour.</em></p></div><div><h5>Tags</h5></div></div></div>","author":"Iain Treloar","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"43c2abf778f83bf865c3ac5a2be446c22a0ecea9825e1a5e4a138155b845c9df","category":"Cycling"}